I have integrated cold plunge (typically around 59°f) into my routine for 2 weeks straight. This water is FREEZING at 50° and completely takes my breath away. However, I’m able to compose & hold my breath for 20 second increments & after 3 minutes, I’m out & I’m soaring! No better way to start my day than w/ the mental & physical accomplishment this provides.. along w/ all the other health benefits! 
 
SWIPE TO SEE! I bought a thermometer for accuracy… brrr!!

#coldplunge #athlete #brr

Move over almonds there’s a new nut in town who brings BIG FLAVOR! Worth saving this recipe for sure. Maybe this post will inspire you to get a run in, knowing you’d face plant into homemade cookies & toasted walnut milk after.. 

Inspired yet? 

Preheat oven 350° & toast your walnuts (DRY) for 20 minutes, shaking the pan after 15. You want them toasty! Cool completely, submerge in water w/ splash of vanilla & trickle of honey, tiny pinch of salt. Blend, strain & refrigerate. THEN. Get your run gear on even when you don’t feel like it. The milk will be chilled, the cookies will be warm.. you are reminded that everything is working out for you. 

#chef #nutrition #triathlon #triathlontraining #triathlete #cookies #walnutmilk #healthyrecipes

Ironman 70.3 World Champs has me learning to measure my success not by my split times or overall ranking, but by the progress I have made in just two years and 4 races. I didn’t hit my numbers or placement that I had hoped for but what I did do was recognize my potential and for that I celebrate!

The easiest sugar-free waffle that will please even your pickiest eater. Gluten free & baking powder free (didn’t have any!) I combined almond • orange • thyme • vanilla + a quick blackberry & Earl grey compote, for this one. 

One bowl Recipe: 

2 cups almond flour
2 eggs
1 cup milk of choice 
Splash of quality vanilla 
Lots of orange zest
Lots of fresh thyme
3 tbs EVOO
Pinch of salt 

Turn on waffle maker. Combine ingredients & set aside in the fridge for 10 minutes or so. In a small saucepan combine blackberries • 1 heaping tbs chia seeds • 1/2 cup or so, early grey tea (I had this leftover which added a really nice depth of flavor but you can use water or any liquid) & the juice from the orange, splash of vanilla. Simmer for 10 minutes. Make waffles, top with compote & enjoy as is or drizzle maple syrup! 

#chef #waffles #nutrition #breakfast

Worth SAVING: My nutritious version of an outstanding French dessert called Clafoutis. I omit the sugar all together & increase the vanilla bean & add fresh thyme. I sprinkle powered sugar on at the end for a touch of sweetness — it’s just the right amount! 

Recipe: 

1 cup milk of choice
3 eggs
2 tsp vanilla bean
2 tbs EVOO
2 tbs fresh or dried thyme
1/2 cup all-purpose flour

Preheat the oven to 325°F. Sprinkle fruit of choice in prepared dish of choice (cupcake / cake / loaf). Blend all the ingredients in a blender for 25 seconds and pour into dish. Bake for 30-35 minutes and let set completely. Easy, delicious and good at the end beginning, middle or end of the day 👩🏻‍🍳❤️
